    "long_instructions": "#### Investigate\r\n\r\nFor the main chorus, is using a <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code> block for the <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Clap Breakdown </span> so the measures will line up with the rest of the chorus.\r\n\r\nCan you add an effect to the chorus using a similar strategy? Choose any effect you want, but make sure all of the measures line up! [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=flyout-id:repeat_toolbox---id:repeat_workspace)\r\n\r\nWhen you're finished, your song should have an Effect playing during the final part of the song\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/c1d9f1118758e2a52ef879a7da64182b-image-1743443595096.png)\r\n\r\n> If you're stuck, try clicking the <i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i> icons for hints!",
